cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about multilingual neural machine translation, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses various modeling principles and approaches, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of distributed representations and end-to-end modeling could also make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of parallel corpora, which could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the corpora includes image captions or other visual data.
